MicroRNA (miRNA) dysregulation represents a critical dimension of the molecular pathology of pediatric Burkitt lymphoma (pBL), yet a systematic, quantitative assessment of the miRNA landscape across distinct biological compartments is lacking. To define compartment-specific miRNA signatures, we performed an integrated re-analysis of miRNA-sequencing data from 51 treatment-naïve pBL samples, encompassing matched tumor tissue, exosomal, and cell-free plasma fractions. Using a rigorous analytical pipeline, we applied stringent expression filtering to 2,982 detected miRNAs, yielding 524 high-confidence candidates for differential expression analysis using DESeq2.
Our analysis revealed a fundamental biological principle: compartments specialize in distinct miRNA processing states, not merely in the abundance of identical mature miRNAs. We observed profound molecular partitioning where tumor tissue exclusively retained functional mature miRNAs for intracellular regulation (e.g., miR-7-5p, log₂FC = -18.7, pₐdⱼ = 1.5×10⁻¹³²), while exosomes were strikingly enriched for precursor forms implicated in extracellular communication (e.g., miR-423, log₂FC = +13.4, pₐdⱼ╼ = 2×10⁻⁸⁶). This suggests a model where exosomes may deliver pre-miRNAs for processing in recipient cells. Furthermore, cell-free plasma contained a mixture of both forms and revealed unexpected systemic biology through the significant abundance of liver-specific miR-122-5p, hinting at organ crosstalk in lymphoma pathogenesis.
This "processing state compartmentalization" provides a novel mechanistic framework that explains the complete segregation of compartments in principal component space. Our findings establish a dual-layer model of miRNA distribution in pBL: canonical functional specialization (growth regulators retained, communication molecules exported) is complemented by a deeper, previously unrecognized layer of compartment-specific RNA biogenesis specialization. This refines the framework for compartment-aware biomarker development and offers critical methodological considerations for interpreting extracellular vesicle cargo across the field.

# miRNA-seq Differential Expression Analysis

This repository contains a complete workflow for analyzing miRNA-seq data across **Exosomes (Exo)**, **Tissue (Ti)**, and **CF compartments**. It includes scripts, results, and visualizations of differential expression.

---

## Repository Structure

```text
├── data/  
│   └── processed/          # Count matrices and metadata  
├── figures/                # PCA, heatmaps, volcano plots, boxplots, ternary plots  
├── results/                # DESeq2 differential expression results  
├── scripts/                # R scripts used for analysis  
├── supplementary_data/     # Additional tables, Venn diagram data, and summaries  
└── README.md

Figures

PCA plots: Global miRNA variation across compartments (figures/PCA_miRNA.png)

Heatmaps: Top significant miRNAs (figures/heatmap_top20_miRNA_annot.png)

Volcano plots: Differential expression for each comparison (figures/volcano_exo_vs_cf.png, etc.)

Boxplots: Expression distribution per compartment, separated by Mature vs Precursor (figures/miRNA_boxplot_per_compartment.png)

Ternary plots: miRNA distribution across compartments 

Supplementary Data

All additional data files are in doc/supplementary/:

bowtie_reads_aligned_summary/ — Alignment summaries from Bowtie.

cf_collapsed_mapped/ — CF compartment mapped miRNAs.

exo_collapsed_mapped/ — Exosome compartment mapped miRNAs.

tissue_collapsed_mapped/ — Tissue compartment mapped miRNAs.

fastqc_miRNAs_reads/ — Raw miRNA FastQC reads quality reports.

fastqc_reports_all/ — FastQC reports for all samples.

multiqc_reports_all/ — Combined MultiQC summary of all FastQC reports.

Installation & Requirements

R (≥ 4.2) and the following packages:

# CRAN packages
install.packages(c(
  "ggplot2", "pheatmap", "dplyr", "tidyr", "ggpubr", 
  "RColorBrewer", "ggrepel", "cowplot", "ggtern", "tibble", "forcats"
))

# Bioconductor packages
if (!requireNamespace("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE))
    install.packages("BiocManager")

BiocManager::install("DESeq2")
BiocManager::install("VennDiagram")

Usage

Place the processed count matrix and metadata in data/processed/.

Run the R scripts from the scripts/ folder. Each script is annotated step-by-step for:

Loading and preprocessing data

Differential expression analysis (DESeq2)

Generating PCA, heatmaps, volcano plots, boxplots, ternary plots, and correlation plots

Results are saved in results/ and figures/. Supplementary tables are in supplementary_data/.

